{{Italic title}}
'''''Wildlife Wars: My Fight to Save Africa's Natural Treasures''''' is a book written by [[Richard Leakey]] and Virginia Morell. Book was published in 2001 by St. Martin's Press.

==Overview-==

It tells of how Leakey had been director of [[National Museums of Kenya|National Museum]] when appointed in 1989, President [[Daniel arap Moi]] appointed him to run the [[Kenya Wildlife Service]]. This was an entirely new experience to Leakey, because he had been accustomed to studying [[Hominidae|hominids]], not managing wildlife. Elephant poaching had been a major problem in the Kenyan National Parks, and the book tells of his efforts to stop it, sometimes with a danger to his life. 

==Reception==
The book was reviewed in the journal ''Endangered Species'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.umich.edu/~esupdate/mayjun2002/heinen.htm |title=Book Review - Wildlife Wars: My Fight to Save Africa's Natural Treasures. |work=Endangered Species |author=Joel T. Heinen |date=June 2002 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref> the [[American Library Association|ALA]] magazine ''[[Booklist]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/5092600/adult-books-nonfiction |title=Adult Books |work=[[Booklist]] |author=Nancy Bent |date=August 2001 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Publishers Weekly]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.publishersweekly.com/978-0-312-20626-0 |title=Wildlife Wars: My Fight to Save Africa's Natural Treasures |work=[[Publishers Weekly]] |author=Charlotte Abbott |date=July 16, 2001 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref> ''[[Books in Canada]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.booksincanada.com/article_view.asp?id=3007 |title=A Political Animal |work=Books in Canada |author=Christopher Ondaatje |date=Winter 2002 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref> ''[[African Business]]'',<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.highbeam.com/doc/1G1-79829769.html |title=Wildlife Wars: My Fight to Save Africa's Natural Treasures |work=[[African Business]] |author=Stephen Williams |date=November 2001 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref> the [[ Royal Geographical Society]]'s ''[[Geographical (magazine)|Geographical]]'' magazine.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://connection.ebscohost.com/c/book-reviews/5329296/tusk-force-leader |title=Tusk Force Leader |work=[[Geographical (magazine)|Geographical]] |author=Nigel Winser |date=October 2001 |accessdate=March 4, 2015}}</ref>

